 │     └── meeting/
 │           ├── index/
 │           ├── service/
 │           ├── module/
 │           ├── dto/
 ├── routes/
 ├── utils/
 └── app.js

---

## Database Design

### Users Table

| Column | Type |
|--------|------|
| id | Integer (PK) |
| name | String |
| email | String (Unique) |

### Meetings Table

| Column | Type |
|--------|------|
| id | Integer (PK) |
| title | String |
| userId | Integer (FK) |
| startTime | DateTime |
| endTime | DateTime |

---

## Business Rules

No overlapping meetings allowed.

Conflict condition:

existing.startTime < new.endTime  
AND  
existing.endTime > new.startTime  

If conflict exists:

400 Bad Request  
"Time slot already booked"

Conflict logic implemented inside service layer.

---

## API Documentation

### Create User

POST /users

Request:

{
  "name": "Deepak",
  "email": "deepak@gmail.com"
}

---

### Get User

GET /users/:id

---

### Create Meeting

POST /meetings

Request:

{
  "title": "Team Meeting",
  "userId": 1,
  "startTime": "2026-02-24T10:00:00",
  "endTime": "2026-02-24T11:00:00"
}

---

### List Meetings

GET /meetings

Optional filters:

GET /meetings?userId=1  
GET /meetings?start=2026-02-24T00:00:00&end=2026-02-25T00:00:00

---

### Get Meeting

GET /meetings/:id

---

### Update Meeting

PUT /meetings/:id

---

### Delete Meeting

DELETE /meetings/:id

